g.text: UML Diagram: DataType Selector in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.
- The use of the data type is represented here by a dotted line (not formal UML).
- The arrows of the inheritance tree are

a.title: ― ObjectAttributeSelector: A resource which describes a specific attribute of an object. It is defined in the style of selectors of the Web Annotation Vocabulary, see https://www.w3.org/TR/annotation-vocab/. The selector can be nested dependent on the structure of the referenced object.
